  "texts": [
    "(6.9)For the case where α is empty, □ β p → □ δ ♢ γ p is valid over F iff F satisfies ∀x∀y(xR δ y → ∃u(yR γ u ∧ xR β u)).",
    "(6.10)For local correspondents, replace ∀x in (6.9) and (6.10) with ∀x ⊑ x 0 so x 0 is free.Proof.",
    "Suppose F satisfies (6.9).",
    "Further suppose that there is a model M based on F and an x ∈ M such that M, x ⊮ □ δ ♢ γ p. Then as in Figure 6.1, there is a y ′ such that xR δ y ′ and M, y ′ ⊮ ♢ γ p, i.e., M, y ′ ⊮ ¬□ γ ¬p, so there is a y ⊑ y ′ such that M, y ⊩ □ γ ¬p.",
    "By R-down, xR δ y ′ implies xR δ y."
